[The serotype of _Salmonella enterica_ has not been stated. Mayonnaise is a thick, creamy dressing often used as a condiment and is a stable emulsion of oil, egg yolk, and either vinegar or lemon juice. The egg is the likely source here. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4078371,5396.]
